The paper deals with the design and analysis of an underwater optical communication system, which involves the use of wireless optical links and RF links. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a decode-and-forward relay, which is a common technique in the field of wireless communication and networking. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the modeling and analysis of the underwater optical turbulence, which suggests that it may also belong to the Optics (cs.OH) sub-category.
